Hydrograph Development Notebooks: Data Exploration¶

Overview: This notebook was created to document data exploration of the availability/applicability of USGS gage Data in the vicinity of the levees in Binghamton, NY.

Read in Gage Data¶

(Downloaded using GageExplorer)

In [3]:
data_dir =os.path.join(os.path.abspath(os.path.join(os.getcwd(), os.pardir)), 'data')
tsvs = glob(os.path.join(data_dir, '015*')) # All gage IDls in this study share the prefix 015
metadata = os.path.join(data_dir ,'gage_metadata.csv')

if metadata in tsvs:
    tsvs.remove(metadata)
    
meta = pd.read_csv(metadata, sep = '\t').style
meta

Merge & Format Gage Data¶

In [4]:
df = MergeDatsets(tsvs) 
print("\nGageID", 'Station Data'.rjust(30), 'First Available Record'.rjust(73), '\n')

for col in df.columns:
    print(col, '\t', legend_dict[col].ljust(55), '\t', str(df[col].first_valid_index()).ljust(10))
    
df.replace(-999999.00, np.nan, inplace=True) # Reformat NaN Values

gage = '01503000_00060_dv'
df_peaks, peaks = Get_USGS_Peaks(state, gage.split('_')[0])
idx_a = df_peaks['peak_cd'].isnull()  # Get only non-flagged data          
data = pd.to_numeric(df_peaks[idx_a]['peak_va'].values)
PeaksPlot(peaks, str(gage.split('_')[0] + ' ' +legend_dict[gage]))
